{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WReF1PWgfm9q5hoxnxC9Z5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Player Profile Context - App-level state management for player profiles\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Provides access to:\n     5→ * - Current user's profile (when wallet connected)\n     6→ * - Profile lookup for other players\n     7→ * - Profile mutations (username, avatar, socials)\n     8→ * - Loot claiming\n     9→ * - Mini profile modal state\n    10→ * - Display helpers\n    11→ */\n    12→\n    13→import {\n    14→  createContext,\n    15→  useContext,\n    16→  useState,\n    17→  useEffect,\n    18→  useCallback,\n    19→  type ReactNode,\n    20→} from \"react\";\n    21→import { useWallet } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n    22→import type {\n    23→  AvatarId,\n    24→  BorderStyle,\n    25→  PlayerProfile,\n    26→  PlayerProfileContextValue,\n    27→} from \"../types\";\n    28→import { AVATAR_CONFIGS } from \"../types\";\n    29→import { getBorderStyleFromLevel } from \"../utils/xp-calculator\";\n    30→import { profileEventBus } from \"../utils/profile-event-bus\";\n    31→import {\n    32→  initializeProfileStore,\n    33→  getProfile as getProfileFromStore,\n    34→  getOrCreateProfile,\n    35→  updateUsername as updateUsernameInStore,\n    36→  updateAvatar as updateAvatarInStore,\n    37→  connectDiscord as connectDiscordInStore,\n    38→  disconnectDiscord as disconnectDiscordInStore,\n    39→  connectTwitter as connectTwitterInStore,\n    40→  disconnectTwitter as disconnectTwitterInStore,\n    41→  claimLoot as claimLootFromStore,\n    42→  claimAllLoot as claimAllLootFromStore,\n    43→  recordGameResult,\n    44→  subscribeToProfiles,\n    45→  getDisplayName as getDisplayNameFromStore,\n    46→  getAvatarId as getAvatarIdFromStore,\n    47→  truncateAddress,\n    48→} from \"../utils/mock-simulation\";\n    49→\n    50→// ============ Context ============\n    51→\n    52→const PlayerProfileContext = createContext<PlayerProfileContextValue | null>(null);\n    53→\n    54→// ============ Provider ============\n    55→\n    56→interface PlayerProfileProviderProps {\n    57→  children: ReactNode;\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→export function PlayerProfileProvider({ children }: PlayerProfileProviderProps) {\n    61→  const { address } = useWallet();\n    62→\n    63→  // State\n    64→  const [myProfile, setMyProfile] = useState<PlayerProfile | null>(null);\n    65→  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);\n    66→  const [selectedProfileAddress, setSelectedProfileAddress] = useState<string | null>(null);\n    67→\n    68→  // Initialize store on mount\n    69→  useEffect(() => {\n    70→    initializeProfileStore();\n    71→    setLoading(false);\n    72→  }, []);\n    73→\n    74→  // Load/create profile when wallet connects\n    75→  // Force level 100 for the connected wallet (testing purposes)\n    76→  useEffect(() => {\n    77→    if (address) {\n    78→      const profile = getOrCreateProfile(address, 100);\n    79→      setMyProfile(profile);\n    80→    } else {\n    81→      setMyProfile(null);\n    82→    }\n    83→  }, [address]);\n    84→\n    85→  // Subscribe to profile updates\n    86→  useEffect(() => {\n    87→    const unsubscribe = subscribeToProfiles((updatedAddress, profile) => {\n    88→      if (updatedAddress === address) {\n    89→        setMyProfile(profile);\n    90→      }"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EydLtiHqaYQnrjxSZpp45Y","session_id":"82717d21-cff7-43a1-a235-f97f60a95616","uuid":"ea372cdf-1a4e-4d72-8495-b00eaa6746a9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01EydLtiHqaYQnrjxSZpp45Y","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a complete picture. Let me compile all the non-deterministic elements found:\n\n## Completion Report\n\nI've thoroughly analyzed the home page and identified **all non-deterministic visual elements** that cause different output on each page load. Here are my findings:\n\n---\n\n### **NON-DETERMINISTIC ELEMENTS FOUND:**\n\n#### **1. Shooting Stars Animation (CSS-based, but timing-dependent)**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx`\n- **Lines**: 290-295\n- **Issue**: Five shooting star elements with different animation delays (5s, 25s, 45s, 65s, 85s) on a 100s loop\n- **CSS**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/index.css` lines 213-262\n- **Impact**: Stars appear at different positions depending on when the page loads relative to the animation cycle\n- **Why non-deterministic**: CSS animations start from page load time, so their visual state differs on each load\n\n#### **2. Campfire Flame Animation**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx` line 402\n- **CSS**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/index.css` lines 676, 685-687\n- **Issue**: 0.6s looping sprite animation (`campfireFlicker`) - visual state depends on load timing\n- **Impact**: Flame sprite frame varies on each page load\n\n#### **3. RNG Buff Indicator Timer**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/boss-raid/components/RNGBuffIndicator.tsx`\n- **Lines**: 18-21, 43-44\n- **Issue**: Uses `Date.now()` to calculate remaining time - displays different countdown on each render\n- **Impact**: Timer shows different values based on current time\n\n#### **4. Leaderboard Generation (HomePage not directly affected, but LeaderboardPage uses Math.random)**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/App.tsx`\n- **Lines**: 519-529 (function `generateLeaderboardData`)\n- **Issue**: Line 525 uses `Math.random()` to generate wagered amounts: `Math.round(baseWager * (0.7 + Math.random() * 0.6) * 100) / 100`\n- **Impact**: Leaderboard data changes on every mount (though this is on `/leaderboard` route, not home)\n\n#### **5. Player Profile Random Generation**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/player-profile/utils/mock-simulation.ts`\n- **Lines affected**:\n  - Lines 40-43: `generateRandomUsername()` uses `Math.random()`\n  - Lines 51-62: `generateRandomLevel()` uses `Math.random()`\n  - Lines 71-72: `getRandomUnlockedAvatar()` uses `Math.random()`\n  - Lines 122, 133-140, 155-178: Mock profile initialization uses `Math.random()` for stats\n  - Line 182: `username: generateRandomUsername()` - every new profile gets random username\n  - Lines 215-216: Profile creation uses `Math.random()` for XP variance\n  - Line 371: Transaction ID generation uses `Math.random()`\n  - Line 406: Loot ID generation uses `Math.random()`\n- **Impact**: \n  - Demo player profiles in chat (lines 313-331 in App.tsx) get randomly generated data\n  - Any new player address rendered gets a random username, level, avatar, and stats\n  - This affects the compact avatars shown in the global chat on the home page\n\n#### **6. Boss Raid Context (Time-based State)**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/boss-raid/context/BossRaidContext.tsx`\n- **Issue**: Uses `Date.now()` for raid timing calculations\n- **Impact**: Boss HP bar, timer, and phase state vary based on current time\n\n#### **7. Dragon Boss Avatar Animations (SVG animate elements)**\n- **Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/boss-raid/components/KrakenAvatar.tsx`\n- **Lines**: Multiple `<animate>` elements throughout (